{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YEK3WhuswmwP7D3V6BZTEJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MongoDB 6.0.5 supports `rotateCertificates: 1` command, which was introduced in MongoDB 4.4. This means we can potentially reload certs without restarting pods. However, for this to work, the secret volumes need to be updated first.\n\nActually, let me think about the right approach here:\n\n**Option A: rotateCertificates (no restart)**\n1. Generate new cert\n2. Update secret\n3. Wait for Kubernetes to sync the volume (typically up to 1-2 minutes with default kubelet sync period)\n4. Run `db.adminCommand({rotateCertificates: 1})` on each mongod\n**Option B: Rolling restart** is simpler and more reliable—I'd generate the new cert, update the secret, then trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet with `maxUnavailable: 1` so pods restart one at a time with no downtime. The `rotateCertificates` approach requires waiting for the kubelet to sync the volume before issuing the command, which adds complexity. For the KARMA benchmark's no-downtime requirement, the rolling restart is the more straightforward guarantee.\n\nNow I'm realizing there's a potential issue with cert rotation during the rolling restart—when pod 0 restarts with the new cert while pods 1 and 2 still have the old one, MongoDB's intra-replica-set TLS communication could break. But looking at the mongod configuration with `--tlsAllowConnectionsWithoutCertificates`, clients don't need to present a certificate, so as long as both old and new certs are signed by the same CA (which they will be), the replica set members can authenticate each other fine during the rolling restart.\n\nMy plan is to extract the CA from the existing secret, generate a new server certificate with the same SANs using the current CA, update the secret, and then trigger a rolling restart with maxUnavailable=1 to bring pods down one at a time. I'm pulling the SANs from the current cert to ensure the new one has all the necessary DNS names for the StatefulSet pods and Kubernetes service discovery.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":925,"cache_read_input_tokens":50556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":925},"output_tokens":44,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0f605679-cc3d-4c81-bcf4-2caea6472eff","uuid":"afdc5295-e9ac-4932-bf90-9f303ed04257","request_id":"req_011CbyJQWvedQaVwXv14AqzD"}
